  "text": "There are examples of non-trivial block coverings in finite groups. Such examples occur in some sporadic simple groups: M 11 , M 22 , M 23 , M 24 , Co 2 , J 4 , B, M . (See e.g. Section 3 in [CITATION_1] ). Also there are examples in some quasisimple groups of Lie type, where t is the defining characteristic. In [CITATION_2] all occurencies of block coverings of the principal t-block in arbitrary finite groups are listed.",
