  "bib_entries": {
    "121775901": {
      "title": "Block separations and inclusions",
      "abstract": "Abstract We investigate the separation of characters by blocks at different primes and the inclusions of q -blocks in p -blocks (viewed as sets of characters), and use these notions to prove results on the structure of the corresponding groups. In particular, we provide a new criterion for the nilpotence of a finite group G based on the separation by principal blocks, and we show that a condition on block unions has strong structural consequences."
